          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target used was natural LiF of thickness",
                "100 mu-g/cm**2 evaporated onto a carbon backing with",
                "a thickness of 50 mu-g/cm**2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SIBAR",
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two telescopes (delta E-E) of",
                "silicon surface barrier detectors were placed on one",
                "of the movable arms inside a 1 m diameter scattering",
                "chamber. The detector thicknesses were 50, 40, 1000",
                "and 1500 micrometer for delta E1, delta E2, E1 and E2",
                "detectors respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE",
                "BCINT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "The angular distributions of charged",
                "particles were measured in the angular range of",
                "Theta lab = 10 to 40 degree.",
                "The beam intensity was measured using a precision",
                "current integrator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The measured elastic scattering angular",
                "distribution data were analysed using the optical",
                "model. All the optical model calculations were",
                "performed using the code FRESCO by taking into",
                "account the proper symmetrisation due to the",
                "identical nature of target-projectile nuclei."
              ]
            }
          ],
